│                                                                                                                                                                                       │
│ Actually, the correct LLVM way to handle this is to use `BasicBlock::getTerminator()` when you want to insert before the terminator, or just use the basic block itself when you want │
│ to insert at the end. But in this context, we want to insert after `LastInst`, which if it's the last non-terminator instruction, should be before the terminator.                    │
